Tony (IO20671@MAINE.MAINE.EDU) wrote:
: Just looking for some monoalphabetic substitution cipher text to
: practice on...and maybe a few (relatively) simple Vigeneres also.

A very readable book is

Elementary Cryptanalysis
Abraham Sinkov
The Mathematical Association of America, Washington DC, 1966.

The book is still in print available directly from MAA. It includes a lot 
of problems with solutions, so you can get some practice.


Bill

